5. What are Generics in Java?
Generics allow you to parameterize types. They enable types (classes and methods) to be parameters when defining classes
, interfaces, and methods, providing stronger type checks at compile time. 
6. Benefits of using Generics: 

	• Type Safety: Catches type errors at compile time rather than runtime. 
	• Elimination of Casts: No need to manually cast objects when retrieving them from a collection. 
	• Code Reusability: Allows you to write algorithms that work on different types. 

